1
00:00:07,633 --> 00:00:10,980
<i>12th Century, China.</i>

2
00:00:10,980 --> 00:00:15,650
<i>The Northern Song Dynasty was in disarray.</i>

3
00:00:15,650 --> 00:00:18,625
<i>The emperor had no interest in governing,</i>

4
00:00:18,625 --> 00:00:24,200
<i>and officials indulged
in bribery and corruption.</i>

5
00:00:24,200 --> 00:00:27,545
<i>Those who advocated for change
were deemed rebels,</i>

6
00:00:27,545 --> 00:00:30,655
<i>and all who revolted were quelled instantly.</i>

7
00:00:31,755 --> 00:00:35,480
<i>The citizens,
faced with taxation and poverty,</i>

8
00:00:35,480 --> 00:00:39,101
<i>became village-plundering bandits,</i>

9
00:00:39,101 --> 00:00:41,681
<i>perpetuating a cycle of robbery and terror.</i>

10
00:00:42,835 --> 00:00:46,850
<i>Yet the militia,
who were to protect their people,</i>

11
00:00:46,850 --> 00:00:49,471
<i>choose instead to act
as accomplice to these thieves,</i>

12
00:00:49,471 --> 00:00:53,031
<i>and helped transport
their stolen loot-turned-bribes.</i>

13
00:00:59,335 --> 00:01:01,730
These tributes are for Sir Gao Qiu.

14
00:01:01,730 --> 00:01:03,200
Carry them with utmost caution!

15
00:01:03,200 --> 00:01:05,055
Yes, sir!

16
00:01:05,055 --> 00:01:08,415
[Imperial Guard]

17
00:01:09,370 --> 00:01:13,990
[Yuncheng, Northern Song]

18
00:01:22,913 --> 00:01:24,943
Ready?

19
00:01:26,575 --> 00:01:28,150
Halt.

20
00:01:28,150 --> 00:01:29,980
Who goes there? Move aside.

21
00:01:29,980 --> 00:01:31,480
Pardon us, sir.

22
00:01:31,480 --> 00:01:33,810
But our wagon has lost a wheel.

23
00:01:33,810 --> 00:01:35,730
The three of us alone cannot carry it aside.

24
00:01:35,730 --> 00:01:38,005
Assist them at once.

25
00:01:38,005 --> 00:01:39,475
Yes, sir.

26
00:01:41,415 --> 00:01:42,950
Move.

27
00:01:42,950 --> 00:01:44,420
Get this wagon aside.

28
00:01:49,225 --> 00:01:52,210
Retreat!

29
00:01:52,210 --> 00:01:54,620
Fire!

30
00:02:24,150 --> 00:02:26,630
Fight!

31
00:02:29,205 --> 00:02:32,250
It's the Pagoda-Shifting Heavenly King!

32
00:02:32,250 --> 00:02:36,840
Villain, you dare plunder our people's taxes?

33
00:02:38,495 --> 00:02:41,550
Your soldiers are not the cowards.

34
00:02:41,550 --> 00:02:44,540
They run, because you are the coward.

35
00:02:45,650 --> 00:02:50,210
Cowards lose their men, and their money.

36
00:02:56,965 --> 00:02:58,200
We found them!

37
00:02:58,200 --> 00:03:00,500
They're right here, sir!

38
00:03:14,915 --> 00:03:17,440
The year cursed us with barely any rain.

39
00:03:17,440 --> 00:03:19,900
Our people suffer from taxation as well.
[Song Jiang, Yuncheng Clerk]

40
00:03:19,900 --> 00:03:25,305
Yet bandits steal whatever foods remain.
[Song Jiang, Yuncheng Clerk]

41
00:03:25,305 --> 00:03:28,295
Perhaps the heavens themselves
have forsaken us.

42
00:03:29,270 --> 00:03:30,870
Are you alright?

43
00:03:35,422 --> 00:03:38,822
You'd best look where you're going, lass.

44
00:03:40,530 --> 00:03:42,620
No, she cannot see.

45
00:03:44,115 --> 00:03:46,910
Would you like to buy a flower, sir?

46
00:03:46,910 --> 00:03:48,295
What?

47
00:03:48,295 --> 00:03:50,605
A flower, you say?

48
00:03:52,955 --> 00:03:54,990
Smell that.

49
00:03:54,990 --> 00:03:58,360
[Lu Zhi Shen, Monk]

50
00:03:59,240 --> 00:04:01,370
These are sprigs of mint.

51
00:04:03,137 --> 00:04:08,027
She has mistaken the scent
for that of a flower.

52
00:04:08,750 --> 00:04:11,510
I see.

53
00:04:13,520 --> 00:04:18,920
I prefer these herbs
over any beautiful flower.

54
00:04:20,440 --> 00:04:22,010
Here.

55
00:04:25,080 --> 00:04:27,180
They smell quite refined, no?

56
00:04:30,745 --> 00:04:34,520
I shall buy your entire stock, lass.

57
00:04:34,520 --> 00:04:38,175
- Everything she has, Song Jiang?
- That's right.

58
00:04:38,175 --> 00:04:39,935
Thank you.

59
00:04:40,989 --> 00:04:43,064
Sir... Song Jiang?

60
00:04:44,143 --> 00:04:45,453
Yes.

61
00:04:47,166 --> 00:04:48,946
There.

62
00:04:50,960 --> 00:04:53,040
Careful now.

63
00:05:04,345 --> 00:05:08,980
[Yuncheng]

64
00:05:08,980 --> 00:05:13,750
[Yuncheng Administrative Office]

65
00:05:13,750 --> 00:05:16,950
Remember, bright smile!

66
00:05:23,330 --> 00:05:25,660
Bring us the booze!

67
00:05:28,625 --> 00:05:30,240
Apologies for the wait, sirs.

68
00:05:30,240 --> 00:05:33,230
You damned slowpoke!

69
00:05:33,230 --> 00:05:37,010
Song Jiang, you must entertain our guests.

70
00:05:37,010 --> 00:05:39,460
These soldiers act as though
this were a tavern.

71
00:05:39,460 --> 00:05:41,370
They carry our people's taxes with them.

72
00:05:41,370 --> 00:05:44,690
We must be grateful for their hard work.

73
00:05:44,690 --> 00:05:48,190
Any child could tell you
they carry bribes, not taxes.

74
00:05:48,190 --> 00:05:50,020
That is the role of the militia.

75
00:05:50,020 --> 00:05:52,850
They'll demand booze and meat at every stop,

76
00:05:52,850 --> 00:05:55,375
and those who refuse them will only perish!

77
00:05:55,375 --> 00:05:58,525
Hey! Where's the alcohol?

78
00:05:58,525 --> 00:06:01,590
Forgive us, sir. We'll bring it right over.

79
00:06:01,590 --> 00:06:03,460
Emergency! Emergency!

80
00:06:03,460 --> 00:06:04,830
Sir, it's an emergency!

81
00:06:04,830 --> 00:06:06,440
What is it?

82
00:06:06,440 --> 00:06:09,790
A neighboring village has fallen to bandits.

83
00:06:09,790 --> 00:06:12,570
What's the commotion?

84
00:06:12,570 --> 00:06:14,255
Sir, I plead your assistance.

85
00:06:14,255 --> 00:06:17,150
A neighboring village is being plundered.

86
00:06:17,150 --> 00:06:19,560
Would you please lend us your assistance?

87
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:21,755
How utterly ridiculous.

88
00:06:21,755 --> 00:06:25,770
We're busy transporting these precious taxes.

89
00:06:25,770 --> 00:06:30,310
We have no orders to protect any villages.

90
00:06:30,310 --> 00:06:31,685
These are lives we can save, sir.

91
00:06:31,685 --> 00:06:35,610
Song Jiang, these men are busy.

92
00:06:35,610 --> 00:06:38,810
Yuncheng has its share of warriors, no?

93
00:06:38,810 --> 00:06:42,890
They are currently on their rounds,
and will not return in time.

94
00:06:42,890 --> 00:06:44,345
- Sir, please!
- Silence!

95
00:06:44,345 --> 00:06:48,150
We are duty-bound to transport these taxes!

96
00:06:48,150 --> 00:06:52,095
Sir, do you truly transport
our people's taxes with you?

97
00:06:52,095 --> 00:06:54,490
You're ruining the taste of my booze.

98
00:06:54,490 --> 00:07:00,070
Get him out of my sight!

99
00:07:00,070 --> 00:07:02,480
Take him away!

100
00:07:02,480 --> 00:07:04,868
Go on, go on.

101
00:07:06,075 --> 00:07:08,950
Where is this village you speak of?

102
00:07:08,950 --> 00:07:11,220
It is the very one we visited days ago.

103
00:07:22,129 --> 00:07:23,559
Sir?

104
00:07:30,915 --> 00:07:32,254
Hello?

105
00:07:33,334 --> 00:07:35,999
Is there anyone left alive?

106
00:07:35,999 --> 00:07:38,039
Hello?

107
00:07:41,370 --> 00:07:42,830
Lass!

108
00:07:43,790 --> 00:07:46,250
She's still breathing!

109
00:07:47,690 --> 00:07:50,620
Pull through, lass. Can you see us?

110
00:07:52,660 --> 00:07:54,910
She's suffered a fatal injury.

111
00:08:01,500 --> 00:08:03,410
What is it?

112
00:08:05,900 --> 00:08:08,500
I can't hear you. Speak up!

113
00:08:12,150 --> 00:08:14,170
Flowers...

114
00:08:14,960 --> 00:08:18,510
Sir Song Jiang...

115
00:08:43,720 --> 00:08:45,290
Lass!

116
00:08:49,410 --> 00:08:51,370
Lass!

117
00:09:28,906 --> 00:09:32,936
[The people are suffering...]

118
00:09:33,835 --> 00:09:36,159
<i>The people are suffering.</i>

119
00:09:36,159 --> 00:09:41,310
<i>And all turn a blind eye to this fact.</i>

120
00:09:41,310 --> 00:09:43,690
<i>I was once the very same.</i>

121
00:09:43,690 --> 00:09:50,230
<i>Yet when I felt the warmth of a child's life
fade away in my arms,</i>

122
00:09:50,230 --> 00:09:56,471
<i>something within me finally snapped.</i>

123
00:09:56,471 --> 00:10:01,770
<i>Our government and militia
refuse to acknowledge our citizens.</i>

124
00:10:01,770 --> 00:10:05,772
<i>Our citizens,
who are dying to bandits and poverty.</i>

125
00:10:05,772 --> 00:10:10,177
<i>We have none to blame for this fate,
but this very country.</i>

126
00:10:10,177 --> 00:10:15,202
<i>This rotten country of ours
killed that very child.</i>

127
00:10:15,202 --> 00:10:17,930
<i>I must question my very purpose</i>

128
00:10:17,930 --> 00:10:21,149
<i>by complying to this corruption
through my ignorance.</i>

129
00:10:21,149 --> 00:10:23,600
<i>Humans who die accomplishing nothing</i>

130
00:10:23,600 --> 00:10:28,753
<i>have served no better purpose
than the trees that surround us.</i>

131
00:10:28,753 --> 00:10:32,560
<i>No, even trodden mint leaves</i>

132
00:10:32,560 --> 00:10:38,095
<i>emit a refined scent,
in all their stubbornness.</i>

133
00:10:38,095 --> 00:10:41,935
<i>No longer will I
rely on the heavens to strike.</i>

134
00:10:59,995 --> 00:11:01,760
<i>I will take action myself.</i>

135
00:11:01,760 --> 00:11:06,520
<i>For if heaven refuses to send aid,
then we, the people must act.</i>

136
00:11:06,520 --> 00:11:09,375
<i>And I will fight with like-minded individuals</i>

137
00:11:09,375 --> 00:11:15,245
<i>till this country changes itself anew.</i>

138
00:11:29,490 --> 00:11:31,960
[Enforcing the Way in Heaven's Name]

139
00:11:42,490 --> 00:11:50,170
I pray this will be the beacon
to illuminate the dark of this land.

140
00:11:53,666 --> 00:11:59,016
Friend, won't you deliver my message
to our comrades of the light?

141
00:12:35,881 --> 00:12:39,501
[Five Years Later]

142
00:12:40,435 --> 00:12:45,950
[Dongjing Kaifeng, Capital of Northern Song]

143
00:12:45,950 --> 00:12:49,660
[Imperial Guard]

144
00:12:51,300 --> 00:12:56,400
[Imperial Guard, Parade Ground]

145
00:13:03,225 --> 00:13:07,520
[Wang Jin, Martial Arts Instructor]

146
00:13:07,520 --> 00:13:09,385
[Militia]
[Imperial Guard]

147
00:13:09,385 --> 00:13:14,475
[Episode 1]

148
00:13:21,600 --> 00:13:23,250
Do you grow bored?

149
00:13:26,530 --> 00:13:28,950
Come at me with whatever you desire.

150
00:13:36,885 --> 00:13:38,230
[Lin Chong, Spearman Instructor]

151
00:13:38,230 --> 00:13:40,350
Stand!

152
00:13:40,350 --> 00:13:42,310
And you call yourself an Imperial Guard?

153
00:13:42,310 --> 00:13:45,742
These are simple exercises.
[Imperial Guard: The emperor's own soldiers]

154
00:13:45,742 --> 00:13:50,190
Remember your duty to protect our emperor.

155
00:13:50,190 --> 00:13:51,795
Hey!

156
00:13:51,795 --> 00:13:55,165
Protect him, from what?

157
00:14:01,150 --> 00:14:04,010
You submitted another request, sir?

158
00:14:05,215 --> 00:14:07,980
Don't look so dissatisfied, Lin Chong.

159
00:14:07,980 --> 00:14:12,290
While I think it fine to test our trainees,

160
00:14:12,290 --> 00:14:15,980
if we impose such a trial,
none will join the Guard.

161
00:14:15,980 --> 00:14:17,525
Why so?

162
00:14:17,525 --> 00:14:20,195
Because all will fail.

163
00:14:21,305 --> 00:14:23,600
And that is fine.

164
00:14:23,600 --> 00:14:26,810
The Imperial Guard must remain strong.

165
00:14:26,810 --> 00:14:29,795
We cannot humor such coddled individuals.

166
00:14:29,795 --> 00:14:34,675
Then we shall garner the resentment
from those such people.

167
00:14:38,525 --> 00:14:40,240
You make a fair point.

168
00:14:40,240 --> 00:14:44,390
Someone will eventually see
the merit to my ways.

169
00:14:44,390 --> 00:14:46,175
"Someone"?

170
00:14:46,175 --> 00:14:48,405
You cannot mean Gao Qiu, do you?

171
00:14:49,715 --> 00:14:52,900
He is the very definition of "coddled".

172
00:14:52,900 --> 00:14:54,540
Enough.

173
00:14:55,705 --> 00:14:58,270
It is my nature to be uptight.

174
00:14:58,270 --> 00:15:00,040
I cannot change that.

175
00:15:04,640 --> 00:15:06,540
They're here. Pull over.

176
00:15:12,440 --> 00:15:14,370
[Cargo]

177
00:15:18,845 --> 00:15:20,940
Is this all you are carrying?

178
00:15:20,940 --> 00:15:22,470
Yes, sir.

179
00:15:24,290 --> 00:15:25,890
Then you may pass.

180
00:15:34,300 --> 00:15:38,000
[Ruan Xiao Wu, Fisherman]

181
00:15:52,325 --> 00:15:53,900
[Ruan Xiao Er, Fisherman]
[Ruan Xiao Qi, Fisherman]

182
00:15:53,900 --> 00:15:56,390
Brother, what are you doing?

183
00:15:57,200 --> 00:16:01,500
Nothing tastes better than smuggled salt.

184
00:16:17,435 --> 00:16:24,070
Do we meet in a bamboo glade
so I am less capable of defending myself?

185
00:16:24,070 --> 00:16:26,605
You may be at ease, good sir.

186
00:16:26,605 --> 00:16:30,115
I am one known as Lu Zhi Shen.

187
00:16:32,790 --> 00:16:35,140
A mere test will not change the country.

188
00:16:37,335 --> 00:16:42,770
You, a stranger,
will complain about my methods as well?

189
00:16:42,770 --> 00:16:45,780
Though you can reignite an unlit candle,

190
00:16:45,780 --> 00:16:49,490
you cannot gather its ashes
to make a candle anew.

191
00:16:49,490 --> 00:16:51,300
I'm afraid I don't follow.

192
00:16:51,300 --> 00:16:53,875
Reforming the Imperial Guard
will not change this country.

193
00:16:53,875 --> 00:16:56,780
I wish to revolutionize this country,

194
00:16:56,780 --> 00:16:59,460
with a like-minded fellow such as yourself.

195
00:17:00,850 --> 00:17:03,100
And what do you suggest I do?

196
00:17:10,125 --> 00:17:13,410
I have come to hand you this.

197
00:17:13,410 --> 00:17:15,700
"Enforcing the Way in Heaven's Name"?

198
00:17:15,700 --> 00:17:21,800
If heaven has forsaken us,
then we must take action ourselves.

199
00:17:22,545 --> 00:17:25,030
"We".

200
00:17:25,030 --> 00:17:27,220
You have others recruited to your cause?

201
00:17:29,820 --> 00:17:32,250
I cannot accept these writings of yours.

202
00:17:43,675 --> 00:17:46,400
Carry that in, carefully.

203
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:48,630
Don't you dare drop our load!

204
00:17:53,320 --> 00:17:57,740
[Chao Gai, Bandit King]
If it touches water, it's gone forever!

205
00:17:59,580 --> 00:18:02,930
I'm surprised you can read
in such darkness, sir.

206
00:18:04,660 --> 00:18:08,260
Why do you continue to reread these writings?

207
00:18:10,757 --> 00:18:15,677
Find me the man who wrote this, Wu Yong.

208
00:18:15,677 --> 00:18:17,514
If I may ask, why?
[Wu Yong, Private Tutor]

209
00:18:23,520 --> 00:18:26,170
Because he is a dangerous man.

210
00:18:27,200 --> 00:18:29,140
So you will kill him?

211
00:18:30,020 --> 00:18:33,830
Go, find him.

212
00:18:41,530 --> 00:18:44,280
[Enforcing the Way in Heaven's Name]

213
00:18:45,175 --> 00:18:48,990
<i>Song Jiang continued to play
the incompetent official,</i>

214
00:18:48,990 --> 00:18:54,295
<i>all while gathering comrades
to one day strike against the country.</i>

215
00:18:54,295 --> 00:18:57,255
<i>Would you like to buy a flower?</i>

216
00:18:58,610 --> 00:19:01,220
<i>Sir... Song Jiang?</i>

217
00:19:04,305 --> 00:19:06,960
Song Jiang.

218
00:19:06,960 --> 00:19:09,940
You called, Xu Li?

219
00:19:09,940 --> 00:19:13,250
You've used the wrong character here.

220
00:19:13,250 --> 00:19:15,820
My apologies, sir. I'll fix it right away.

221
00:19:15,820 --> 00:19:20,060
You've misspelled a name as well, how rude.

222
00:19:20,060 --> 00:19:23,200
I shall fix that as well.

223
00:19:23,200 --> 00:19:25,230
And please, fix your attire.

224
00:19:25,230 --> 00:19:26,825
My attire?

225
00:19:26,825 --> 00:19:29,635
Your sleeves, they have ink on them!

226
00:19:30,895 --> 00:19:31,940
I am a clumsy fellow, sir.

227
00:19:31,940 --> 00:19:34,525
How do you get ink on your sleeves?

228
00:19:34,525 --> 00:19:35,979
Even children know to keep tidy.

229
00:19:35,979 --> 00:19:40,490
Sir, about these villages here...

230
00:19:40,490 --> 00:19:44,305
They've all been plundered
by the Pagoda-Shifting Heavenly King, no?

231
00:19:44,305 --> 00:19:46,521
Yes, what of it?

232
00:19:46,521 --> 00:19:49,260
I'm simply perplexed.

233
00:19:49,260 --> 00:19:52,900
Not a single villager
was killed in the attack.

234
00:19:52,900 --> 00:19:55,115
What are you getting at?

235
00:19:55,115 --> 00:19:59,475
Why did his troop not attack
the surrounding villages as well?

236
00:20:00,645 --> 00:20:04,280
All the other bandits show no mercy.

237
00:20:04,280 --> 00:20:08,520
And it's far easier to loot villages
than attack the Imperial Guard.

238
00:20:09,505 --> 00:20:11,860
Who cares what a bandit is thinking?

239
00:20:11,860 --> 00:20:13,960
You must fix your attire at once!

240
00:20:13,960 --> 00:20:17,080
Yes, sir.
I shall handle the rest of our work.

241
00:20:17,080 --> 00:20:20,040
Folks, please. Feel free to head on home.

242
00:20:20,040 --> 00:20:22,270
- I better not see another mistake.
- Yes, sir.

243
00:20:22,270 --> 00:20:25,660
It takes double the time to fix them.

244
00:20:25,660 --> 00:20:27,120
I understand, sir.

245
00:20:27,120 --> 00:20:29,210
- Now don't keep Lian Lian waiting.
- Right.

246
00:20:29,210 --> 00:20:31,315
I mean, enough!

247
00:20:31,315 --> 00:20:34,205
- You'd best do well, you understand?
- Yes, sir.

248
00:20:50,584 --> 00:20:56,600
[Look into the Pagoda-Shifting Heavenly King]

249
00:20:56,600 --> 00:20:59,050
I am the Pagoda-Shifting Heavenly King!

250
00:20:59,050 --> 00:21:02,185
Leave your carriages and wagons here!

251
00:21:02,185 --> 00:21:05,025
We'll capture you today, villain!

252
00:21:06,635 --> 00:21:09,120
- I'm next.
- No, it's my turn!

253
00:21:09,120 --> 00:21:13,130
I am the Pagoda-Shifting Heavenly King!

254
00:21:13,130 --> 00:21:14,990
- No, I am!
- I am!

255
00:21:14,990 --> 00:21:20,650
No, I am!
[Pagoda-Shifting Heavenly King]

256
00:21:20,650 --> 00:21:24,920
- I'm the Pagoda-Shifting Heavenly King!
- No, me!

257
00:21:24,920 --> 00:21:28,595
I am the Pagoda-Shifting Heavenly King!

258
00:21:28,595 --> 00:21:33,475
I am the Pagoda-Shifting Heavenly King!

259
00:21:37,785 --> 00:21:40,980
What do you mean, "harsh treatment"?

260
00:21:40,980 --> 00:21:43,310
It is my duty to cultivate capable soldiers.

261
00:21:43,310 --> 00:21:48,190
Yet you ignore those who pay you a bribe.
[Gao Qiu, General of the Imperial Guard]

262
00:21:48,190 --> 00:21:49,420
A bribe?

263
00:21:49,420 --> 00:21:51,870
I heard about your proposal.

264
00:21:51,870 --> 00:21:54,690
Mandate a test to join the Guard, is it?

265
00:21:54,690 --> 00:21:58,730
What a clever way to fill your own pockets.

266
00:21:58,730 --> 00:22:01,860
You misunderstand my intentions, sir.

267
00:22:01,860 --> 00:22:06,520
As a martial instructor,
it is my duty to test our guards.

268
00:22:06,520 --> 00:22:11,940
So your one word will decide
whether they can join or not?

269
00:22:11,940 --> 00:22:16,086
As general of the Imperial Guard,

270
00:22:16,086 --> 00:22:22,516
it is my duty to worry
about the potential of corruption.

271
00:22:23,385 --> 00:22:26,370
Though you may be general,

272
00:22:26,370 --> 00:22:29,240
you have disrespected me so, sir.

273
00:22:29,240 --> 00:22:32,225
Rescind your proposal of a test.

274
00:22:32,225 --> 00:22:35,245
- General Gao Qiu...
- Return to your assigned duties!

275
00:22:35,960 --> 00:22:38,410
Am I clear, Master Wang Jin?

276
00:22:50,105 --> 00:22:51,332
My apologies, sir.

277
00:22:51,332 --> 00:22:52,725
Not to worry.

278
00:22:54,910 --> 00:22:57,370
I take no offense.

279
00:22:57,370 --> 00:23:00,450
If you shall excuse me.

280
00:23:01,196 --> 00:23:02,836
Yes, of course.

281
00:23:20,285 --> 00:23:21,830
Welcome home, Dear.

282
00:23:21,830 --> 00:23:23,020
Yeah.

283
00:23:23,020 --> 00:23:25,135
Will you be having dinner tonight?

284
00:23:25,135 --> 00:23:27,045
I already ate.

285
00:23:27,785 --> 00:23:28,920
Then how about some tea?

286
00:23:28,920 --> 00:23:31,031
My wife.

287
00:23:31,031 --> 00:23:32,831
Please, leave me be.

288
00:23:43,520 --> 00:23:47,550
[Zhang Lan, Lin Chong's wife]

289
00:23:55,769 --> 00:24:02,500
[General Lv Rong has been captured.
Master Wang Jin is in danger]

290
00:24:02,500 --> 00:24:04,460
Master Wang Jin...

291
00:24:13,270 --> 00:24:15,210
Master, you must run.

292
00:24:17,375 --> 00:24:19,460
Run, you say?

293
00:24:19,460 --> 00:24:21,405
Prepare to leave at once.

294
00:24:21,405 --> 00:24:23,645
Take your mother with you.

295
00:24:25,270 --> 00:24:27,360
I do not understand.

296
00:24:28,165 --> 00:24:33,610
Your close friend, General Lv Rong,
has been captured as a suspected rebel.

297
00:24:33,610 --> 00:24:36,945
He is to serve as an example
to the rest of the rebels.

298
00:24:36,945 --> 00:24:39,025
Master, you will be next.

299
00:24:42,620 --> 00:24:46,000
How do you suggest
I escape with my elderly mother?

300
00:24:49,705 --> 00:24:52,080
I shall make all necessary arrangements.

301
00:24:52,080 --> 00:24:55,210
I've already taken your stead
outside our walls.

302
00:24:55,210 --> 00:24:56,680
Lin Chong...

303
00:24:56,680 --> 00:24:58,385
Master, you must knock me out.

304
00:24:58,385 --> 00:25:02,335
Our every movement is being monitored now.

305
00:25:10,475 --> 00:25:13,370
I only see apprentices around.

306
00:25:13,370 --> 00:25:15,775
A spy is hidden among them.

307
00:25:15,775 --> 00:25:17,685
Now, hurry!

308
00:25:21,990 --> 00:25:24,160
You have my gratitude, Lin Chong.

309
00:25:27,160 --> 00:25:31,250
Take this as a token of appreciation,
from one martial artist to another.

310
00:26:05,405 --> 00:26:07,020
This is where we part ways.

311
00:26:07,020 --> 00:26:10,840
It will only be temporary.

312
00:26:12,120 --> 00:26:16,580
I pray that you remain well.

313
00:26:22,780 --> 00:26:25,250
I won't hear our staffs cross again.

314
00:26:26,750 --> 00:26:28,430
Farewell.

315
00:26:48,290 --> 00:26:52,160
Farewells are always a difficult endeavor.

316
00:26:54,580 --> 00:26:56,220
No.

317
00:26:57,420 --> 00:27:00,430
He has reminded me
good friends are a blessing.

318
00:27:01,505 --> 00:27:04,206
That is why I shed tears for our parting.

319
00:27:04,206 --> 00:27:06,520
You must thank life for those bonds.

320
00:27:06,520 --> 00:27:08,335
[Madame Wang, Wang Jin's mother]

321
00:27:08,335 --> 00:27:14,750
The reason why you cry
for a friend you must part with,

322
00:27:14,750 --> 00:27:19,040
is because you lived a fulfilling life,

323
00:27:19,870 --> 00:27:21,430
Jin.

324
00:27:23,450 --> 00:27:28,430
He is a man I am proud to call a friend.

325
00:27:45,230 --> 00:27:47,010
Welcome home.

326
00:27:48,395 --> 00:27:51,080
You waited all night?

327
00:27:51,080 --> 00:27:55,430
You were never one to return at dawn...

328
00:27:56,560 --> 00:27:58,430
Well, I am now home safe.

329
00:27:59,335 --> 00:28:02,680
Rest. A night without sleep is taxing.

330
00:28:37,696 --> 00:28:39,526
What are you doing?

331
00:28:42,480 --> 00:28:47,460
I am mimicking my wet nurse.

332
00:28:48,740 --> 00:28:53,130
She used to comfort me in this way.

333
00:28:55,837 --> 00:28:57,607
Why?

334
00:29:01,740 --> 00:29:06,390
Because you looked quite lonely, my dear.

335
00:30:09,351 --> 00:30:14,991
You smell of winter daphne's.

336
00:30:36,060 --> 00:30:40,480
[Yan Po Xi, traveling entertainer]

337
00:31:06,740 --> 00:31:08,510
Yan Xin!

338
00:31:09,480 --> 00:31:12,020
[Ma Gui, Song Jiang's Spy]

339
00:31:13,715 --> 00:31:15,580
Ma Gui?

340
00:31:15,580 --> 00:31:17,761
I see Bai Lan is here as well.

341
00:31:17,761 --> 00:31:19,896
But where is Yan Xin?

342
00:31:19,896 --> 00:31:21,506
Come, this way.

343
00:31:22,330 --> 00:31:23,830
Bai Lan.

344
00:31:33,286 --> 00:31:35,462
My husband has died.

345
00:31:37,080 --> 00:31:41,390
This is what he left for you.

346
00:31:48,690 --> 00:31:53,970
Yan Xin was an excellent spy.

347
00:31:55,385 --> 00:31:58,080
I will not ask how he passed.

348
00:31:58,080 --> 00:32:01,630
But I shall keep his spirit close to heart.

349
00:32:03,696 --> 00:32:07,806
As well as this memento he has left me.

350
00:32:11,456 --> 00:32:16,796
Master Wang Jin has safely escaped
the Imperial Guard.

351
00:32:18,165 --> 00:32:19,750
Ma Gui?

352
00:32:19,750 --> 00:32:25,340
I shall take over my husband's mantle.

353
00:32:43,095 --> 00:32:47,080
[Li Fu]
[Qinglian Temple, Intelligence Organization]

354
00:32:47,080 --> 00:32:50,970
Your instruction is on par with Wang Jin.

355
00:32:53,426 --> 00:32:58,876
How does it feel to sit
in your mentor's throne?

356
00:32:59,700 --> 00:33:01,410
You are?

357
00:33:03,916 --> 00:33:06,026
First, I would like to ask one thing.

358
00:33:06,825 --> 00:33:10,120
Do you know where Wang Jin has gone?

359
00:33:10,120 --> 00:33:12,440
No. I have denied this countless times.

360
00:33:14,830 --> 00:33:17,160
Then one more question.

361
00:33:18,040 --> 00:33:23,720
Have you heard word of a monk
Wang Jin met in a bamboo grove?

362
00:33:26,160 --> 00:33:29,000
I will take anything you know.

363
00:33:36,080 --> 00:33:37,800
No, I cannot say I have.

364
00:33:46,395 --> 00:33:54,390
I hear a competent soldier was slain
outside these very walls.

365
00:33:57,538 --> 00:34:00,808
All while carrying his elderly mother
on his back.

366
00:34:05,060 --> 00:34:08,100
What a stunt, I say.

367
00:34:24,825 --> 00:34:26,175
Excuse me, sir.

368
00:34:27,275 --> 00:34:29,130
I come bearing news about this author.

369
00:34:29,130 --> 00:34:31,340
Oh? So you found him?

370
00:34:31,340 --> 00:34:32,359
No, sir.

371
00:34:32,359 --> 00:34:38,075
But a mysterious monk handed
the same writings to one of our subordinates.

372
00:34:55,455 --> 00:34:57,870
The very same script.

373
00:34:57,870 --> 00:35:01,220
Let us keep an eye on this monk.

374
00:35:02,105 --> 00:35:04,290
Sir, you are
the Pagoda-Shifting Heavenly King.

375
00:35:04,290 --> 00:35:08,620
Why bother with the author of this text?

376
00:35:12,110 --> 00:35:15,050
Read it, and you will understand.

377
00:35:31,625 --> 00:35:33,620
Why have you come?

378
00:35:33,620 --> 00:35:36,989
You must leave at once.

379
00:35:36,989 --> 00:35:38,404
What?

380
00:35:38,404 --> 00:35:43,764
Sir Song Jiang insists you are in danger.

381
00:35:49,095 --> 00:35:51,460
Alright.

382
00:35:51,460 --> 00:35:53,050
When?

383
00:35:53,855 --> 00:35:55,810
Tonight.

384
00:35:55,810 --> 00:35:58,730
I've stationed my men outside these walls.

385
00:35:58,730 --> 00:36:01,440
I cannot leave so easily. I rather stand out.

386
00:36:01,440 --> 00:36:05,400
When night falls, come to the barrack walls
as you did with Wang Jin.

387
00:36:05,400 --> 00:36:07,870
You shall be safe there.

388
00:36:07,870 --> 00:36:10,550
And bring your wife with you.

389
00:36:10,550 --> 00:36:11,835
Zhang Lan?

390
00:36:11,835 --> 00:36:13,895
She is equally in danger.

391
00:36:15,045 --> 00:36:17,150
What danger?

392
00:36:17,150 --> 00:36:23,430
Our marriage was a cover,
to make it look as though I've settled down.

393
00:36:25,143 --> 00:36:30,120
As things stand, Zhang Lan will...

394
00:36:30,120 --> 00:36:32,695
Things aren't going well between you two?

395
00:36:32,695 --> 00:36:34,485
The very opposite.

396
00:36:35,426 --> 00:36:37,206
Zhang Lan...

397
00:36:38,760 --> 00:36:41,620
She has surrendered her heart to me.

398
00:37:07,760 --> 00:37:09,840
Who is this man?

399
00:37:14,300 --> 00:37:17,390
He was a messenger for Sir Gao Qiu.

400
00:37:27,000 --> 00:37:29,500
An invitation to a meal.

401
00:37:30,410 --> 00:37:32,830
Did this man make any note of that?

402
00:37:33,625 --> 00:37:37,380
No, he declared he came to have his fun.

403
00:37:37,380 --> 00:37:39,340
A damn trap!

404
00:37:40,230 --> 00:37:45,180
I will be charged
for murdering Gao Qiu's messenger.

405
00:37:53,625 --> 00:37:56,580
Let us claim he violated me.

406
00:37:56,580 --> 00:37:59,400
That is why you cut him down.

407
00:37:59,400 --> 00:38:03,790
But imagine the looks people would give you!

408
00:38:03,790 --> 00:38:06,975
You killed a man for my sake.

409
00:38:06,975 --> 00:38:11,435
And I must reciprocate
that love you've shown me.

410
00:38:15,660 --> 00:38:17,390
Zhang Lan...

411
00:38:19,030 --> 00:38:21,090
Listen to me.

412
00:38:31,540 --> 00:38:35,440
I only masquerade as a spearman instructor.

413
00:38:35,440 --> 00:38:40,810
In truth, I work for a man named Song Jiang.

414
00:38:41,820 --> 00:38:44,220
To change this country for the better.

415
00:38:45,950 --> 00:38:47,830
Change this country?

416
00:38:50,545 --> 00:38:53,070
I will now escape this place.

417
00:38:53,070 --> 00:38:57,190
You will stay here as a woman
abandoned by her husband.

418
00:38:57,190 --> 00:39:00,875
You are my home, Dear.

419
00:39:00,875 --> 00:39:06,010
I do not care who you truly are.

420
00:39:08,130 --> 00:39:09,750
Why?

421
00:39:11,000 --> 00:39:15,600
Why love a man like myself?

422
00:39:19,310 --> 00:39:22,430
You act like you know it all,

423
00:39:23,606 --> 00:39:26,166
yet you know nothing.

424
00:39:29,870 --> 00:39:35,080
Love does not need a reason, my dear.

425
00:39:38,800 --> 00:39:40,800
Zhang Lan...

426
00:39:48,920 --> 00:39:50,470
I...

427
00:40:16,975 --> 00:40:19,020
Song Jiang!

428
00:40:19,020 --> 00:40:20,925
Lin Chong has been apprehended.

429
00:40:20,925 --> 00:40:23,935
You must leave this village at once!

430
00:40:25,160 --> 00:40:26,970
That, I cannot do.

431
00:40:27,705 --> 00:40:32,870
If I escape,
Lin Chong will have no place to return home.

432
00:40:32,870 --> 00:40:35,060
I will remain right here.

433
00:40:35,750 --> 00:40:38,800
Lin Chong knows your name.

434
00:40:39,885 --> 00:40:44,330
He would never give that intel away.

435
00:40:44,330 --> 00:40:45,595
I understand your conviction,

436
00:40:45,595 --> 00:40:50,685
but if we lose you,
what will become of our movement?

437
00:40:52,015 --> 00:40:54,850
If my death ends this movement,

438
00:40:54,850 --> 00:40:59,540
then that is all my ambitions
ever amounted to.

439
00:40:59,540 --> 00:41:03,280
You can avoid death,
yet choose to face it willingly.

440
00:41:03,280 --> 00:41:05,900
Is that not betraying
those very ambitions of yours?

441
00:41:05,900 --> 00:41:07,000
Lu Zhi Shen.

442
00:41:07,000 --> 00:41:09,605
You are also betraying your comrades!

443
00:41:09,605 --> 00:41:13,675
How can I preach a great cause
without even trusting my own men?

444
00:41:15,190 --> 00:41:19,100
I will choose to believe in Lin Chong.

445
00:41:34,750 --> 00:41:37,050
Lin Chong.

446
00:41:38,270 --> 00:41:41,641
I see you have received quite the beating.

447
00:41:41,641 --> 00:41:45,370
Your wife, Zhang Lan, was it?

448
00:41:45,370 --> 00:41:49,465
She continues to plead your innocence.

449
00:41:49,465 --> 00:41:53,556
I did not know he was a messenger
of General Gao Qiu's.

450
00:41:53,556 --> 00:41:55,555
I am well aware.

451
00:41:55,555 --> 00:42:01,355
No fool would knowingly murder
a messenger of the general.

452
00:42:02,005 --> 00:42:04,870
You believe my words?

453
00:42:04,870 --> 00:42:07,020
But of course.

454
00:42:07,020 --> 00:42:08,475
Sir Li Fu...

455
00:42:08,475 --> 00:42:13,155
I am the one who sent that messenger
to be slain by your hands.

456
00:42:14,480 --> 00:42:16,100
What?

457
00:42:18,305 --> 00:42:21,620
Locusts are dangerous pests to keep around.

458
00:42:21,620 --> 00:42:26,010
Two will immediately propagate,
and become a plantation-killing drove.

459
00:42:31,035 --> 00:42:35,678
These writings light a fire
in people's hearts.

460
00:42:35,678 --> 00:42:39,918
It has even inspired
a loyal countryman as myself.

461
00:42:39,918 --> 00:42:41,718
I...

462
00:42:44,660 --> 00:42:47,850
I am only a spearsmanship instructor.

463
00:42:53,356 --> 00:42:57,006
You share Wang Jin's eyes.

464
00:42:58,040 --> 00:43:00,670
The eyes of a locust.

465
00:43:03,630 --> 00:43:06,170
Who wrote these scriptures?

466
00:43:06,910 --> 00:43:08,310
Tell me.

467
00:43:09,455 --> 00:43:13,520
Or else we shall torture Zhang Lan.

468
00:43:13,520 --> 00:43:15,120
That woman...

469
00:43:16,710 --> 00:43:19,510
She knows nothing!

470
00:43:24,570 --> 00:43:26,990
Come, this way.

471
00:43:39,740 --> 00:43:43,070
So you are Zhang Lan.

472
00:43:45,330 --> 00:43:50,430
You are indeed quite the beauty.

473
00:43:54,500 --> 00:43:58,000
Do you wish to save Lin Chong's life?

474
00:43:59,450 --> 00:44:00,800
Yes, sir.

475
00:44:01,656 --> 00:44:05,346
No matter the method?

476
00:44:06,730 --> 00:44:08,160
Yes, sir.

477
00:44:10,165 --> 00:44:14,310
Then you know what you must do.

478
00:44:14,310 --> 00:44:16,430
Do you not?

479
00:44:23,330 --> 00:44:26,050
If I am able to save my husband...

480
00:44:28,407 --> 00:44:31,337
Then I fear nothing.

481
00:44:33,520 --> 00:44:35,910
Undo your garments.

482
00:44:48,080 --> 00:44:50,440
Keep going.

483
00:45:21,125 --> 00:45:24,190
Guards!

484
00:45:24,190 --> 00:45:25,850
General Gao Qiu!

485
00:45:31,150 --> 00:45:33,730
What a cowardly man.

486
00:45:34,410 --> 00:45:36,527
Do you think a woman like myself...

487
00:45:37,285 --> 00:45:40,170
would be able to kill a man like you?

488
00:45:40,170 --> 00:45:42,330
What?

489
00:45:42,330 --> 00:45:45,270
Lin Chong is innocent!

490
00:45:45,270 --> 00:45:50,395
You have taken my husband's life hostage,

491
00:45:50,395 --> 00:45:53,385
in hopes of violating me.

492
00:45:55,305 --> 00:46:01,000
Where is the justice
in this capital of Kaifeng?

493
00:46:10,915 --> 00:46:14,020
<i>I only masquerade as a spearman instructor.</i>

494
00:46:14,020 --> 00:46:19,180
<i>In truth, I work for a man named Song Jiang.</i>

495
00:46:20,295 --> 00:46:23,370
<i>To change this country for the better.</i>

496
00:46:23,370 --> 00:46:26,040
If I had known sooner...

497
00:46:28,626 --> 00:46:30,846
I would have been able to support you.

498
00:46:34,650 --> 00:46:36,550
What are you doing?

499
00:46:39,020 --> 00:46:40,810
My dear...

500
00:46:42,700 --> 00:46:44,500
Do I...

501
00:46:47,060 --> 00:46:52,040
still smell of winter daphne's?

502
00:46:53,880 --> 00:46:55,510
Stop!

503
00:47:03,100 --> 00:47:04,540
Enough.

504
00:47:06,535 --> 00:47:10,116
Terrible news, Lin Chong.

505
00:47:10,116 --> 00:47:13,516
Your woman has died.

506
00:47:17,375 --> 00:47:19,320
What?

507
00:47:19,320 --> 00:47:21,225
Why does that bother you?

508
00:47:21,225 --> 00:47:22,740
How did she die?

509
00:47:22,740 --> 00:47:25,190
She killed herself.

510
00:47:25,190 --> 00:47:28,715
Put a knife to her neck, and sliced.

511
00:47:28,715 --> 00:47:33,275
You succumbed to lust,
and attempted to violate her.

512
00:47:34,035 --> 00:47:37,160
So what if I did?

513
00:47:37,160 --> 00:47:40,944
Did you not check her belongings beforehand?

514
00:47:40,944 --> 00:47:45,254
Or perhaps you never thought
his wife would be wielding a knife.

515
00:47:46,110 --> 00:47:52,470
Does the Qinglian Temple underestimate me
after gaining Cai Jing's favor?

516
00:47:54,360 --> 00:47:56,220
What were her...

517
00:47:59,125 --> 00:48:04,130
What were Zhang Lan's last words?

518
00:48:04,130 --> 00:48:05,840
Come again?

519
00:48:07,305 --> 00:48:09,290
Her last words.

520
00:48:09,290 --> 00:48:10,960
I don't know.

521
00:48:11,795 --> 00:48:15,240
She asked if she still smelled
of winter daphne's.

522
00:48:15,240 --> 00:48:18,340
- If memory serves correctly, that is.
- Silence!

523
00:48:20,170 --> 00:48:24,970
Now that his beloved has died,
no amount of torture will get him to speak.

524
00:48:26,520 --> 00:48:32,040
Even death turns a beauty
into a hunk of meat.

525
00:48:34,530 --> 00:48:36,630
No, I...

526
00:48:48,650 --> 00:48:51,410
I failed to notice...

527
00:48:53,450 --> 00:48:55,880
her love for me.

528
00:49:02,600 --> 00:49:06,010
This was to be the start of our future.

529
00:49:16,366 --> 00:49:20,216
Gao Qiu! You bastard!

530
00:49:21,455 --> 00:49:23,710
Gao Qiu!

531
00:49:23,710 --> 00:49:26,040
You bastard!

532
00:49:35,267 --> 00:49:40,440
<i>"If you seek birds,
then why not offer a perch?"</i>

533
00:49:40,440 --> 00:49:44,425
<i>"Birds cannot fly forever, else they'll die."</i>

534
00:49:44,425 --> 00:49:48,185
<i>"If you seek a perch,
come to Liangshan Marsh."</i>

535
00:49:52,410 --> 00:49:54,080
Pardon me.

536
00:50:26,700 --> 00:50:31,830
[Enforcing the Way in Heaven's Name]

537
00:50:53,865 --> 00:50:55,280
Where are you headed to?

538
00:50:55,280 --> 00:50:56,890
Liangshan Marsh.

539
00:50:56,890 --> 00:50:58,330
Why the marsh?

540
00:50:58,330 --> 00:51:00,600
The Pagoda-Shifting Heavenly King
calls for me.

541
00:51:00,600 --> 00:51:01,650
It is too dangerous.

542
00:51:01,650 --> 00:51:06,270
These are bandits who pillage
every last village they come across.

543
00:51:06,270 --> 00:51:10,310
The Pagoda-Shifting Heavenly King
only aims for dirty money.

544
00:51:10,310 --> 00:51:12,005
He's not murdered a single villager.

545
00:51:12,005 --> 00:51:16,435
But why go to see him yourself?

546
00:51:17,505 --> 00:51:23,370
The one who left this note
is telling me two things.

547
00:51:23,370 --> 00:51:27,960
One, they have more intel than us.

548
00:51:28,690 --> 00:51:30,840
And two...

549
00:51:31,955 --> 00:51:37,120
They see the fault in my writings.

550
00:51:37,120 --> 00:51:42,020
If I seek answers,
I am to go to Liangshan Marsh.

551
00:51:58,070 --> 00:51:59,700
There it stands.

552
00:52:01,335 --> 00:52:06,100
Like a stronghold that floats above water.

553
00:52:06,100 --> 00:52:09,125
There are around 2,000 to 3,000 bandits
over yonder.

554
00:52:09,125 --> 00:52:14,945
They are ruled by the man known as Wang Lun.

555
00:52:16,595 --> 00:52:19,940
No, do you intend to storm the place?

556
00:52:19,940 --> 00:52:23,120
Even the militia
struggle to overcome that fortress!

557
00:52:23,120 --> 00:52:26,960
That is the perch
the Pagoda-Shifting Heavenly King refers to.

558
00:52:26,960 --> 00:52:31,026
If our comrades have no base,

559
00:52:31,026 --> 00:52:36,806
then we are doomed to repeat
a tragedy like Lin Chong's.

560
00:52:37,600 --> 00:52:41,380
I will start by building a country there.

561
00:52:42,215 --> 00:52:44,580
Song Jiang...

562
00:52:44,580 --> 00:52:47,090
Though it will be quite the small country,

563
00:52:47,090 --> 00:52:50,845
it will be inhabited
by those with large ambitions.

564
00:52:50,845 --> 00:52:52,485
Yes.

565
00:52:53,690 --> 00:53:00,440
That small country of yours
will one day overtake this rotten one.

566
00:53:11,200 --> 00:53:13,200
I read your writings extensively.

567
00:53:14,786 --> 00:53:16,976
Those who have strong ambitions...

568
00:53:18,642 --> 00:53:21,212
would have their hearts set ablaze by it.

569
00:53:22,620 --> 00:53:27,200
Yet ideals alone cannot shape a country.

570
00:53:29,370 --> 00:53:35,220
When starting a fire,
one must first collect the branches.

571
00:53:36,410 --> 00:53:38,020
Go on.

572
00:53:39,730 --> 00:53:46,210
This is a magnificent text
that will spark inspiration in our men.

573
00:53:47,540 --> 00:53:50,737
Though your ideology is grand,

574
00:53:50,737 --> 00:53:54,197
there is one component that is lacking.

575
00:53:55,370 --> 00:53:59,160
And what may that be,
Pagoda-Shifting Heavenly King?

576
00:54:15,080 --> 00:54:17,040
Myself.

577
00:54:19,055 --> 00:54:20,480
You, sir?

578
00:54:20,480 --> 00:54:22,880
Call me Chao Gai.

579
00:54:24,913 --> 00:54:29,843
I shall become your first branch.

580
00:54:32,620 --> 00:54:34,760
I will give you your country.

581
00:54:51,420 --> 00:54:53,100
Chao Gai.

582
00:54:54,190 --> 00:54:57,390
For starters, a small country will do.

583
00:54:59,090 --> 00:55:00,520
Indeed.

584
00:55:03,276 --> 00:55:05,726
I want that fortress for our cause.

585
00:55:36,587 --> 00:55:39,600
No, Lin Chong will be murdered.

586
00:55:39,600 --> 00:55:41,400
We cannot lose Lin Chong.

587
00:55:41,400 --> 00:55:44,230
Though it is a gamble,
it is not an impossible one.

588
00:55:44,230 --> 00:55:45,480
Enough!

589
00:55:45,480 --> 00:55:47,820
What have you done
aside from write, Song Jiang?

590
00:55:47,820 --> 00:55:49,990
All you've given us is abstract theories.

591
00:55:49,990 --> 00:55:51,660
We of Qinglian Temple will take action.

592
00:55:51,660 --> 00:55:56,980
We shall rebuild this country
from the shadows.

593
00:55:56,980 --> 00:56:00,710
You have grown drunk on your own strength.

594
00:56:00,710 --> 00:56:02,850
You are doomed to die on the battlefield.

595
00:56:02,850 --> 00:56:06,860
A spy like myself
could never become a normal woman.

596
00:56:06,860 --> 00:56:09,580
"Yang Zhi, the Blue-faced Beast"? Not bad.

597
00:56:09,580 --> 00:56:12,289
You order me to abandon a child
who has much in his future?

598
00:56:12,289 --> 00:56:14,134
I do not fear your face.

599
00:56:14,134 --> 00:56:16,424
It is blood I fear the most.

600
00:56:17,190 --> 00:56:21,450
You must save something bigger.

601
00:56:22,415 --> 00:56:25,600
That is to say, this country of ours.

602
00:56:25,600 --> 00:56:27,160
Live!

603
00:56:27,160 --> 00:56:28,870
This is how I create a country.

604
00:56:28,870 --> 00:56:30,150
That is no way to be a king!

605
00:56:30,150 --> 00:56:32,795
Then why else do countries fall to ruin?

606
00:56:32,795 --> 00:56:36,155
Song Jiang!

607
00:58:18,500 --> 00:58:24,190
[Episode 1- FIN]

